--how to create a chart



 Title               =Top Orders by Date
 Type                =Chart
Location             =Local Database
Type                 =SQL Query

                      select to_char(o.order_timestamp,'Mon DD, YYYY')
                      order_day,
SQL Query           =SUM(o.order_total) sales
                     from demo_orders o
                     group by to_char(o.order_timestamp,'Mon DD, YYYY'),
                     order_timestamp
                     order by 2 desc nulls last
                     fetch first 5 rows only
Start New Row       =On (default)
 Column             =Automatic (default)
 Column Span        =  4


Show Region Icon (under
Template Options)

Place a check mark to select this option

Body Height (under Template
Options)

240px (Click OK to close the dialog screen)
Icon fa-lg fa-apex

Click the Attributes node under the new region and set the following properties:
 Type Bar
 Orientation Horizontal
Click the New sub-node under Series and set the following properties:
 Location (under Source) Region Source
 Label ORDER_DAY
 Value SALES
 Type (under Link) Redirect to Page in this application
Click No Link Defined under Target and set the following properties in the Link Builder dialog
box:
 Type Page in this application
 Page 4 (Click OK to close the dialog screen)